In polar coordinates, with the origin at the center of the ellipse and with the angular coordinate formula_52 measured from the major axis, the ellipse's equation is
Reflexive property.
When a ray of light originating from one focus reflects off the inner surface of an ellipse, it always passes through the other focus.
Polar form relative to focus.
